Bugs Found:
1. Explanation: The method maxEncodedSize(int) is not implemented in the BaseEncoding class, which may cause a NullPointerException when used.
   Suggested Fix: public int maxEncodedSize(int len) { return (int) Math.ceil((double) len * getCharBytes()); }
2. Explanation: The method maxDecodedSize(int) is not implemented in the BaseEncoding class, which may cause a NullPointerException when used.
   Suggested Fix: public int maxDecodedSize(int len) { return (int) Math.ceil((double) len / getCharBytes()); }
3. Explanation: The method getCharBytes() is not implemented in the BaseEncoding class, which may cause a NullPointerException when used.
   Suggested Fix: public abstract int getCharBytes();
4. Explanation: The method trimTrailingPadding(CharSequence) is not implemented in the BaseEncoding class, which may cause a NullPointerException when used.
   Suggested Fix: public abstract CharSequence trimTrailingPadding(CharSequence chars);
5. Explanation: The method decodeTo(byte[], CharSequence) is not implemented in the BaseEncoding class, which may cause a NullPointerException when used.
   Suggested Fix: public abstract int decodeTo(byte[] tmp, CharSequence chars);
6. Explanation: The method encodingStream(Writer) and decodingStream(Reader) are not implemented in the BaseEncoding class, which may cause a NullPointerException when used.
   Suggested Fix: public abstract OutputStream encodingStream(Writer writer); public abstract InputStream decodingStream(Reader reader);

